    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p>This pattern is intended to be used with homogeneous volumes and provides a simple way to create volume falloff effects.</p><h4 id=\"PxrRadialDensity-Radius\"><strong>Radius</strong></h4><p>The radius of the gradient</p><h4 id=\"PxrRadialDensity-Density\"><strong>Density</strong></h4><p>The maximum density of the gradient</p><h4 id=\"PxrRadialDensity-Exponent\"><strong>Exponent</strong></h4><p>Controls the shape of the transition from max to min density</p><h4 id=\"PxrRadialDensity-Start\"><strong>Start</strong></h4><p>The start position of the gradient. 0 is the center</p><h4 id=\"PxrRadialDensity-Stop\"><strong>Stop</strong></h4><p>The stop position of the gradient.  1 is the edge  / radius</p><h4 id=\"PxrRadialDensity-CoordinateSystem\">Coordinate System</h4><p>Default to the center of your object's bounding box</p><p><br/></p>"
